      "writtenOn": "2017-04-28T16:21:05Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "a single idea for both buffers: IMO it\u0027s better to use the buffer\u0027s .size() directly instead of maintaining a separate variable to know where it ends and where to append. This way you know:\n- data size is always buffer.size(), no garbage in the end\n- if you need to append anything, just call buffer.insert(buffer.end(), ptr, ptr + size) - this will both copy the data and update buffer size at once\n- just don\u0027t forget to call clear() when restarting buffer processing",
